President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Vermont due to severe storm and flooding that occurred in July 2021. This declaration allows federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. James McPherson has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and further damage assessments warrant it. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.